House’s Frank Asks Supercommittee to Impose Fee on Biggest Banks

-- B y   P h i l   M a t t i n g l y
-- 
2011-10-13T16:40:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/house-s-frank-asks-supercommittee-to-impose-fee-on-biggest-banks.html
U.S. Representative  Barney Frank ,
the top Democrat on the House Financial Services Committee,
asked Congress’s debt-reduction supercommittee to impose a fee
on the biggest banks and hedge funds to help pay down the
federal deficit.  Frank made the request in an Oct. 12 letter to Senator
 Patty Murray  and Representative  Jeb Hensarling , co-chairmen of
the Joint Select Committee on  Deficit Reduction .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Phil Mattingly in Washington at 
 pmattingly@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lawrence Roberts at 
 lroberts13@bloomberg.net  